## Quick Reference

- **Components:** Markdoc treats tags and partials as first-class citizens, so you can define reusable blocks without JavaScript glue.
- **Conditional Text:** Control visibility with familiar `{% if %}` syntax rather than brittle HTML comments.
- **Deployment:** Static builds stay pure Markdown + data, which keeps edge deploys fast and cache-friendly.

## Further Reading

- Read the official Markdoc concepts guide to understand tags, nodes, and layouts.
- Pair the extension with Zed's live preview so writers can spot rendering issues.
- Check in sample components regularly; they double as regression tests whenever the grammar changes.
